gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput

Class GlobalPickSender

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.GlobalPickSender

  • public final class GlobalPickSender
extends java.lang.Object
    represents a New Global Pick packet which has additional fields. There is a general udp header followed by a payload. The payload is a single space delimited line where ? stands for omitted string elements and 0.0 for omitted numeric elements. The whole message is stored in a bytebuffer.
    The header on the wire is:
    0 msgInst Message institution
    1 msgType A type of message
    2 modId A module ID
    3 fragNum The packet number of the packet, 0=first
    4 msgSeqNum The message sequence number
    5 lastOfMsg Flag indicating this is the last packet in the message
    Global Pick:
    char[32] author String containing either EW logo (TypeModInst) or "US-SomeAuthorString", limit 32 characters
    char space Delimiter
    int sequence Global pick sequence number
    char space Delimiter
    int version Global pick message version number
    char space Delimiter
    char[] station String containing station name aka site, limit 5 characters
    char space Delimiter
    char[] channel String containing channel aka component, limit 3 characters
    char space Delimiter
    char[] network String containing network code, limit 2 characters
    char space Delimiter
    char[] location String containing location code, limit 2 characters
    char space Delimiter
    char[18] pick time String containing the pick time in the form YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.mmm
    char space Delimiter
    char[8] phase name String containing the phase name, limit 8 characters
    char space Delimiter
    double error_window Double containing the symmetrical error window half width
    char space Delimiter
    char polarity Character containing the polarity U or D for up or down
    char space Delimiter
    char onset Character containing the onset, i, e, q for impulsive, emergent, questionable
    char space Delimiter
    char picker_type Character containing the picker type, m = manual, r = raypicker, l = lomax, e = EW, U = UNKNOWN.
    char space Delimiter
    double high_pass Double containing the high pass frequency
    char space Delimiter
    double low_pass Double containing the low pass frequency
    char space Delimiter
    double back_azm Double containing the back azimuth
    char space Delimiter
    double slowness Double containing the slowness
    char space Delimiter
    double snr Double containing the signal to noise ratio
    char space Delimiter
    double amp Double containing the amplitude
    char space Delimiter
    double period Double containing the amplitude period

    • Constructor Detail

      • GlobalPickSender

        public GlobalPickSender(int queueSize,
                        java.lang.String host,
                        int port,
                        java.lang.String mhost,
                        int mport,
                        EdgeThread parent)
        This thread sets up a queue of Global Picks to be sent on a Earthworm wire to the broadcast address to the given port. Optionally the local interface and port can be set as well.
        Parameters:
        queueSize - Number of elements that can be queued
        host - The IP address of the broadcast address for the sub=net
        port - The port to broadcast to
        mhost - Optional, if given this IP address is bound for sending the packets(leave null or "" if no bindings)
        mport - Optional, if not zero, then bind this address on the sender end
        parent - an EdgeThread for logging, or null for console logging.

        public void setThrottleMS(int ms)

        Parameters:

      • queuePick

        public boolean queuePick(java.lang.String author,
                         java.util.GregorianCalendar pickTime,
                         java.lang.String seedname,
                         double amplitude,
                         double period,
                         java.lang.String phase,
                         int sequence,
                         double error_window,
                         java.lang.String polarity,
                         java.lang.String onset,
                         java.lang.String pickerType,
                         double hipassFreq,
                         double lowpassFreq,
                         double backAzm,
                         double slowness,
                         double snr)
        Queue a pick into this object. The return indicates whether space was available to send the pick.
        Parameters:
        author - Character string with author name
        pickTime - The time of the pick
        seedname - NNSSSSSCCCLL for the channel being picked
        amplitude - in um (<=0. omit)
        period - in seconds (<=0. omit)
        phase - A phase code like "P" or "S" limit 8 characters
        sequence - Some sequence number for this this pick. This must be unique for each pick.
        error_window - This is the error window half width (<0 omit)
        polarity - U or D or ?
        onset - i, e, q for impulsive, emergent, questionable
        pickerType - m = manual, r = raypicker, l = lomax, e = EW, s=subspace, U = UNKNOWN. We can add others if we need them
        hipassFreq - Frequency in Hz of high pass filter on picker (<=0. omit)
        lowpassFreq - Frequency in Hz of low pass filter on picker (<=0. omit)
        backAzm - In degrees clockwise from true north (<0. omit)
        slowness - The slowness (<=0. omit)
        snr - The estimated signal to noise ratio (<=0. omit);
        Returns:
        True if the pick was put in the queue, otherwise the pick was not queued and user might want to resubmit later!
